    "## Overlap Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "First we do a basic overlap of terms in subsets - no use of the graph"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 19,
   "id": "951c02fb",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "pairs = list(compare_all_subsets(oi, prefix='GO'))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 20,
   "id": "6c44b896",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def pairs_to_dm(pairs):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Create a distance matrix\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    rows = [(p.set1_id, p.set2_id, 1-p.jaccard_similarity) for p in pairs]\n",
    "    df = pd.DataFrame(rows, columns =['subsetA', 'subsetB', 'sim'])\n",
    "    df = df.pivot(\"subsetA\", \"subsetB\", \"sim\")\n",
    "    return df"
   ]
  },
